                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> It is early in the morning here so take that into account.....<br /><br />I think the problem started at the very creation of the game.  There are just too many classes.  Maybe it would have been better to have fewer base classes each one sharing the same innate ability, but as you level allow you a few options in each one to specialize in, and later a couple areas.  By makeing these specail areas a small tweak to the parent class instead of completely redifining it every one would have still had a useful, but custom character.<br /><br />At this point it is too late to fix it IMO.  This game has had a nice long run, but nothing lasts forever as they say.   <br /><br />Myself I wish I would not have purchased GoD.  I just don't have the time to get well equiped enough to advance there at all or even survive there long in most zones.  I will never see one spell from there or at least not in the next year or so judging by how the spells are gotten, so that carrot really has no lure for me.  I am glad that there is plenty of content for those that have the time and gear to do it, I just would have liked the expansion to have additional content for players of the same level range but do not have VT/elemental/time gear. <br /><br />I do like Jobober getting crits and enraging though, cracks me up every time I see it <img src="images/icon_smile_big.gif" width="15" height="15" border="0" alt="" title="" align="middle" />.<br /></span id="msg"></font></td>
