                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> There's a similar thread going on at the FoH boards. It's called "Pitfalls of balancing around DPS". As a possible solution for the Holly Trinity and the exclusion of many classes out of groups, some people pointed out the possibility of enlarging the group's capacity up to 8 members. This is what I replied to that (literal quote):<br /><br />----------------------<br />To be honest, I'd rather have the mob's DPS tunned down in stead of having 8 men groups. <br /><br />The problem is that SoE directly links challenge with mob's crazy DPS. According to them, in order to increase challenge, they got to increase mob's DPS.... but in the other hand they enforce single pulling by adding monk lulls, pacifications, fading memories, etc.... So, by doing this, the game dulls down into a min/max shit.<br /><br />Braking news! How about if we come back to the old school formula? how about if we have mobs NOT hitting like a Panzer, but they do NOT come in singles every funcking time? Like I said in other thread: braking into the Lord Efreeti room or crawling deep into The Hole with one group back in the day was VERY challenging, and mobs's DPS wasn't that high, so there's got to be another way to deliver challenge upon the players other than multiplying damage output by three fold with each expansion. It's just a huge lack of creativity and balance-foresight from SoE.<br /><br />Seriously, I think it's all going out of whack. It's really stupid that knights cannot tank in one-group events, and it's also really stupid that one cleric cannot outheal the damage in-taking. Talk about unbalance.<br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Yag.<br />--------------------------<br /><br />So, as you can see, in my opinion the problem root aint the existance of key-features such as CH, Slow or Defensive. The problem is that SoE has limited their content (and GoD is the ultimate example of this) to be only possibly beaten by the conjuntion of Slow, CH and Defensive. That's lack of creativity. They go the easy road when it comes to creating new content: they simply pump up DPS with each expansion as a way of keeping up with the "challenge curve", and thus such key-features (Slow, CH, Defensive) remain utter necessary. They dont revamp AI, or mob's social behaviour... they simply fucking grant mobs 2k DPS status. WOOOOT how thilling!<br /><br />Tank+Heal+Slow could be just another hunting strat, just like kitting, AoE'ing or ping-pong agro'ing. Unfortunately, when it comes to the high end content, SoE won't accept any other formula than the mother fucking Tank+Heal+Slow.<br /><br />No wonder this game is getting so old with that non-creative dev team.<br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Yag.</span id="msg"></font></td>
