                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> In regards to the original question, I think option number 2 applies, and exactly for the reason stated by Yaguex.<br /><br />I'd add Charm to the list of abilities that must be unfairly nerfed because of the current design mindset.  Charm would be perfectly fair if mobs were not 800% as effective as regular players under regular circumstances.<br /><br />In the Graffe forums a debate rekindles periodically pitting raid content versus challenging non-raid content.  The only anti-small group argument that rang true in my opinion was the difficultly of designing small encounters to be challenging for all groups.  <br /><br />I suggested alternative routes to the goal for various group compositions.  That is: content like what we have now for Trinity groups, or mazes filled with swarms to lay waste to (for AE groups), or a series of high hp low damage output mobs (for pet groups), a zone with six Trakanons (for kiters), etc.  I was countered on this suggestion by the observation that it would take much longer to design content for various play styles than it does to design content that simply requires 15 clerics and one of every other class.  Which I thought was very true, but also very sad, and not worthy of my time or money.</span id="msg"></font></td>
