                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> &lt;&lt;2. Class imbalance rises from poorly balanced content and is not fundamental to EQ. Namely, the equivalence of hard-hitting mobs with lots of hps with difficulty is the mentality that creates class imbalance. Solutions to this imbalance would involve a rethinking of the way content is designed.&gt;&gt;<br /><br />I feel that is the real problem but one can not overlook some of the issues which lead to it.  Abilities like Defensive, Slow, CH and "single pulling" have played a role in the molding the game enviroment.  What may look like a challenging encounter could become completely trival once those three abilities are taken into account.  So SoE designs encounters with those abilities in mind, then the problem becomes these encounters are nearly impossible without those abilities.<br /><br />Now the problem is these abilities have become so ingrained into EQ, that removing or changing them would cause a huge uproar by various classes.  Not to mention it would mean having to re-evaluate pretty much all high end content.<br /><br /></span id="msg"></font></td>
                    </tr>
