                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> SOE spends very little time tuning the game or even looking at innovative ways to tweak game mechanics. Its all single pull/high DPS mobs that require slow/cheal/defensive. Every other class then competes for the remaining 3 slots. <br /><br />Some options:<br /><br />- multiple mob encounters that stress off tanking, rooting, and/or pet tanking. <br />- variable mobs that randomly reset their abilities so that for 15 minutes the mob may spawn 4 helpers at the first hit, be magic immune, slow immune, etc. so that you can never have a set tactic for the encounter. Mobs should be able to reset their abilities on a timer separate from respawn. <br />- Encounters that require skill chains from multiple classes to accomplish other than tank/slow/cheal. <br />- encounters that require the group to avoid combat prior to reaching the target stressing rogue scouting, levitate, invis, illusions, etc (no, not just pacify your way to target). <br /><br />Personally, I want hard, challenging 6 person content that ANY combination of classes can attempt. I am totally sick of raiding...its too boring, wastes too much time not doing anything, and generally takes way to long. GoD seems right up my alley, but my necro isn't 65 yet and I have yet to see any groups lower than 65 doing any of the trials. The normal outdoor GoD zones are the same boring old content.</span id="msg"></font></td>
