                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> I think one of the big issues that push the holy trinity angle is the fact that SOE has stated, on multiple occassions, that they want to avoid one mob vs one group situations. They've said they aren't truly happy with groups being able to single pull and that they believe a group should have to deal with multiple mobs at one time.<br /><br />That being the case your group needs a healer...your group needs some sort of crowd control...your group needs a tank. Then what you fill out the rest of the group with varies.<br /><br />That being said I also believe a huge part of "class imbalance" comes from players favouring one class over another for personal reasons not practicality.<br /><br />Sure some encounters in game require specific classes while others don't. The best LDoN group I've ever been in was myself, two beastlords, two mages, and a shammy. We did hard adventures with ease. No cleric....no warrior....no chanter.<br /><br />/shrug<br /><br /><br />SOE can only do so much to cater to the players. What do you expect them to do? Releasing mobs that hit for less would trivialize some things...increasing group size would do the same.<br /><br />I really don't believe there's any way around the perception of the class imbalancing and I also believe that perception is somewhat exaggerated from how bad it actually is.<br /></span id="msg"></font></td>
