                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Its the same old story that has plagued most RPGs since the days of Dungeons and Dragons.  Its much easier for DMs (SOE) to create hack and slash type adventures and encounters, because more people will get involved in them.<br /><br />Creating a scenerio that requires the participants to think instead of bash is just too much work, and not enough people will enjoy them it or participate in them because, frankly, a lot of players aren't really that bright. <br /><br />A lot of them are quite intelligent, and would love those type of quests, scenerios, or adventures that requires brain-power, but the unwashed masses would revolt and whine if they had to do anything more mentally challenging than press a couple hotkeys.<br /><br /></span id="msg"></font></td>
