                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> when LDoN first came out i remember putting together my first "high difficulty" group. i did it about the same way i had done many of the normal groups, and we lost.  miserably.  at that point i remember telling myself, next time make sure that you have the PERFECT group, one that contains the holy trinity, because these can't be won w/o them.<br /><br />fast forward a month or 2.  my recent ldon "high difficulty" groups have been anything but the holy trinity.  its true that i like a cleric in the group, but a good druid can keep tanks up as well. for a tank i will look first for a warrior, but i hesitate not a bit in asking a well geared knight to stand in.  there are 4 slowers to choose from, and quite frankly the enchanter is the last slow class i take nowadays.. i prefer the bst, for the offtanking ability of both pet and bst, and also standing in as a 4th dps class. that leaves 3 spots in the group that can be set aside for the remaining 6 pure dps classes, mage, necro, monk, ranger, rogue, wiz.. i like to try to get a monk for the single pulls, obviously.  <br /><br />the real point i am trying to make is.... GoD is crazy difficult, and i understand that desire for the perfect group to go there.. however, it is also very new, and w/ the expansion comes gear upgrades, offensive abilities, etc that may eventually make GoD as trivial as Povalor is now.  as people learn the ins and outs of GoD, i am sure the need for the trinity will loosen as it has done in LDoN and PoP.  there are 2 classes that can heal, 3 that can tank, 4 that can slow, and 6 that can hurt the mob.. imo it all seems pretty fair.</span id="msg"></font></td>
